tools.description:
Analyze and understand audio content. Maximum 10 audios per call.

REQUIRED format — use 'audio_info' array (NOT 'audios' or 'audio_list'):
  {"audio_info": [{"file": "/path/to/audio.mp3", "prompt": "Transcribe this"}]}

Generate videos from text prompts or images. Unified entry point for all video generation.
Max 5 requests per call. Duration: 6 or 10 seconds. Resolution: 768P or 1080P.

REQUIRED format — use 'video_requests' array (NOT 'requests', 'videos', or flat parameters):
  Text-to-video: {"video_requests": [{"prompt": "A cat playing", "output_file": "cat.mp4"}]}
  Image-to-video: {"video_requests": [{"prompt": "Cat runs", "output_file": "run.mp4", "image_file": "cat.png"}]}

Prefer this tool over batch_text_to_video / batch_image_to_video — it handles both T2V and I2V.

Synthesize images from text prompts, with optional reference images for editing/transformation.
Max 10 requests per call.

REQUIRED format — wrap each request in a 'requests' array (do NOT pass prompt as flat parameter):
  {"requests": [{"prompt": "A cute cat", "output_file": "cat.png", "aspect_ratio": "1:1"}]}

For image editing, pass reference images:
  {"requests": [{"prompt": "Make it watercolor style", "input_urls": ["https://..."], "output_file": "out.png"}]}

Analyze images with prompts and return text results.
Max 20 images. Supports: jpeg, png, webp.

REQUIRED format — use 'image_info' array (NOT 'images', 'image_list', or 'image_urls'):
  {"image_info": [{"url": "https://...", "prompt": "Describe this image"}]}
  {"image_info": [{"file": "/absolute/path/to/img.png", "prompt": "OCR this"}]}

Analyze and understand video content. Maximum 10 videos per call.

REQUIRED format — use 'video_info' array (NOT 'video_list', 'videos', or 'tasks'):
  {"video_info": [{"file": "/absolute/path/to/video.mp4", "prompt": "Describe this video"}]}
  {"video_info": [{"url": "https://cdn.example.com/video.mp4", "prompt": "Analyze"}]}
File paths must be absolute (e.g. /Users/...), do NOT use file:// URIs.
